text: Sagar Paresh Udeshi (born 14 October 1986 in Mumbai) is an Indian cricketer. He made his first-class debut for Chilaw Marians Cricket Club in the 2018–19 Premier League Tournament in Sri Lanka on 14 December 2018. He was the leading wicket-taker for Chilaw Marians Cricket Club in the tournament, with 57 dismissals in eight matches. He made his List A debut for Puducherry in the 2018–19 Vijay Hazare Trophy on 19 September 2018. He made his Twenty20 debut on 8 November 2019, for Puducherry in the 2019–20 Syed Mushtaq Ali Trophy. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1986 births Category:Living people Category:Indian cricketers Category:Puducherry cricketers Category:Chilaw Marians Cricket Club cricketers Category:Cricketers from Mumbai
